verbose_text: Changes in temperature, hypoxia, local ischemia, hydrogen peroxide, and osmotic pressures can induce the expression of CIRP, which participates in regulating endometrial cycles, embryonic development, oncogenesis, and hypothermia protecting tumor necrotic factor induced cell apoptosis, in addition to the elevation of recombinant protein yields via its over-expression in recombinant cells [XREF_BIBR - XREF_BIBR].
